    <stitle>International&#174; MaxxForce&#8482; DT, 9 and 10 Engine Service Manual - Power Cylinders - Clean, Inspect,
        and Measure - Measure Pistons
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="measure" graphiccount="3">
        <title>Measure Pistons</title>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Measure Top Compression Ring Grooves</title>
            <table id="t2650208001" tblwidth="pg-wide" type="simple" frame="topbot">
                <title>Piston Ring Gauge Pin Selection Table</title>
                <tgroup cols="3">
                    <colspec colname="col1" colwidth="0.86*"/>
                    <colspec colname="col2" colwidth="1.35*"/>
                    <colspec colname="col3" colwidth="0.81*"/>
                    <tbody>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <title>Engine Rating</title>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <title>Ring / Groove Type</title>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <title>Gauge Pin Diameter</title>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>All MaxxForce&#8482;DT series engines</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Top / keystone cross section</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>2.885 mm (0.1136 in)</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>All MaxxForce&#8482;9 and 10 series engines</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Top / keystone cross section</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>2.70 mm (0.1063 in)</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
            <figure id="f3350015457" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figh04/h04020.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
                <caption>Piston ring groove measurement (top / keystone cross section)</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install
                    <hotlnk document="eges3351_394.xml" xrefid="t335001503">Piston Gauge Pins</hotlnk>
                    <xref refid="t335001503"/>
                    in the top compression ring groove. Make sure the gauge pins are parallel.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">With pistons at room temperature 20 &#176;C (68 &#176;F) measure the diameter of the
                    piston over the gauge pins using an
                    <hotlnk document="eges3351_394.xml" xrefid="t335001503">outside micrometer</hotlnk>
                    <xref refid="t335001503"/>.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">If the top compression ring groove measurement exceeds
                    <hotlnk document="eges3351_T335001501.xml" xrefid="t335001501">Specifications</hotlnk>
                    <xref refid="t335001501"/>
                    replace the piston.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Measure Intermediate and Oil Control Ring Groove</title>
            <figure id="f3350015458" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figh04/h04008.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
                <caption>Measure ring groove (typical)</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Place the edge of a new intermediate compression ring in the middle piston ring groove.
                    Roll the intermediate compression ring all the way around the piston ring groove to ensure the ring
                    is free in its groove.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">With the edge of the intermediate compression ring in the piston intermediate
                    compression ring groove, use a
                    <hotlnk document="eges3351_394.xml" xrefid="t335001503">feeler gauge</hotlnk>
                    <xref refid="t335001503"/>
                    to measure clearance between the ring and groove.
                </para>
                <para>If the intermediate compression ring clearance exceeds
                    <hotlnk document="eges3351_T335001501.xml" xrefid="t335001501">Specification</hotlnk>
                    <xref refid="t335001501"/>, replace the piston.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Place the edge of a new oil control ring in the oil control ring groove. Roll the oil
                    control ring all the way around the piston to ensure the ring is free in its groove.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">With the edge of the oil control ring in the piston oil ring groove, use a
                    <hotlnk document="eges3351_394.xml" xrefid="t335001503">feeler gauge</hotlnk>
                    <xref refid="t335001503"/>
                    to measure clearance between the ring and groove.
                </para>
                <para>If the oil control ring clearance exceeds
                    <hotlnk document="eges3351_T335001501.xml" xrefid="t335001501">Specification</hotlnk>
                    <xref refid="t335001501"/>, replace the piston.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Measure Piston-to-Cylinder Sleeve Running Clearance</title>
            <figure id="f3350015459" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figh04/h04007.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
                <caption>Measure piston skirt diameter (typical)</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">With pistons at room temperature 20 &#176;C (68 &#176;F), use an
                    <hotlnk document="eges3351_394.xml" xrefid="t335001503">outside micrometer</hotlnk>
                    <xref refid="t335001503"/>
                    to measure piston skirt diameter. Place micrometer 90 degrees from the piston pin bore.
                </para>
                <randlist type="bullet">
                    <item>
                        <para>For MaxxForce&#8482;DT aluminum pistons take skirt diameter measurement 28 mm (1.1 in)
                            from the bottom of the piston skirt.
                        </para>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <para>For MaxxForce&#8482;9 and 10 steel pistons take skirt diameter measurement 12 mm (0.47 in)
                            from the bottom of the piston skirt.
                        </para>
                    </item>
                </randlist>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Subtract the piston skirt diameter from the inside diameter of the cylinder sleeve. See
                    <hotlnk document="eges3351_380.xml" xrefid="s1517">Measure Cylinder Sleeves</hotlnk>
                    <xref refid="s1517"/>. The result is the running clearance between the piston and the cylinder
                    sleeve.
                </para>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>Piston to Cylinder Sleeve Running Clearance = Cylinder Sleeve Inside Diameter - Piston
                            Skirt Diameter
                        </para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">If piston to cylinder sleeve running clearance is not within
                    <hotlnk document="eges3351_T335001501.xml" xrefid="t335001501">Specification</hotlnk>
                    <xref refid="t335001501"/>
                    recheck piston and cylinder sleeve measurements and specifications and replace the part that is out
                    of specification.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
